The Director General of Small and Medium Enterprises Development Agency of Nigeria (SMEDAN), Dr. Dikko Umaru Radda, has congratulated Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina State and urged him to rededicate his energy to the Micro Small and Medium Enterprises (MSMEs) subsector. In a congratulatory message to the governor made available to newsmen in Abuja, Dr. Radda described the victory of Governor Masari at the just concluded polls as a reflection of his wide acceptance by the people of Katsina State. “The impact of your government was felt all over the state, and the people of the state really enjoyed the dividend of democracy in the last four years,” he said. While assuring Governor Masari of his unalloyed support and cooperation in the years ahead, he urged him to rededicate his energy to the Micro Small and Medium Enterprises (MSMEs) subsector to create jobs and wealth for the good people of the state.  #SMEDAN flags off Conditional Grant Scheme for SMEs in Bauchi Formalising MSMEs with Conditional Grant Transfer Kano plans cluster for leather biz